<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!--
    ServiceNow Update Set record-definition for the `sys_dictionary` row that
    declares the `status` Choice field on the `x_[scope]_case` custom table
    inside the scoped application `x_[scope]`.

    Per AAP Section 0.5.7 (Data-Model Mapping verbatim):
        Field     Type     Constraints
        status    Choice   Draft, Open, In Progress, Pending, Resolved, Closed

    Per AAP Section 0.1.2 the `case.status` field defaults to `Draft` and
    replaces ArkCase's free-form String column `cm_case_status` (whose
    @PrePersist hook on CaseFile.java line 307-316 silently set
    setStatus("DRAFT") when null/empty). The ServiceNow target preserves
    the same default behavior but at the dictionary level via
    <default_value>Draft</default_value>, which the platform applies on
    every new record - through the form, the Table API, the scripted REST
    submission endpoint at ../portal/rest/sys_ws_definition_x_[scope]_case_submit.xml,
    and the seed scripts under ../seed-data/cases/. Note the case change:
    ArkCase used UPPERCASE "DRAFT"; the ServiceNow target uses Title Case
    "Draft" per AAP Section 0.1.2 verbatim ("`case.status` default = `Draft`").
    The scripts that consume this field MUST compare against the Title Case
    label (e.g., flow trigger filters and Business Rule conditionals).

    THIS FIELD IS THE BACKBONE OF THE ENTIRE STATE-MACHINE. Per AAP Section
    0.5.5, every transition rule is keyed on changes to this field:

       Draft -> Open
            : assigned_group populated
            : ../flows/sub_flows/validate_open_transition.xml
       Open -> In Progress
            : assigned_agent populated AND member of assigned_group
            : ../flows/sub_flows/validate_inprogress_transition.xml
       In Progress -> Pending
            : sets pending_reason (Awaiting Info | Awaiting Third Party | Other)
            : ../flows/sub_flows/validate_pending_transition.xml
       Pending -> In Progress
            : clears pending_reason
            : ../business_rules/x_[scope]_clear_pending_reason_on_inprogress.xml
       In Progress -> Resolved
            : all linked x_[scope]_case_task records have status = Closed
            : ../flows/sub_flows/validate_resolved_transition.xml
            : Failure surfaces VERBATIM blocking error per AAP Section 0.7.4:
              "All tasks must be closed before resolving this case."
       Resolved -> Closed
            : caller has x_[scope]_case_manager role
            : auto-set closed_date = gs.nowDateTime()
            : ../flows/sub_flows/validate_closed_transition.xml
            : ../business_rules/x_[scope]_set_closed_date.xml
       *      -> Draft
            : PROHIBITED (no backward transitions to Draft)
            : ../business_rules/x_[scope]_block_draft_backtransition.xml
            : Failure surfaces VERBATIM blocking error per AAP Section 0.7.4:
              "Cases cannot be returned to Draft."
       Closed -> *
            : PROHIBITED - terminal state
            : ../business_rules/x_[scope]_block_terminal_closed.xml
            : Failure surfaces VERBATIM blocking error per AAP Section 0.7.4:
              "Closed cases are terminal and cannot be modified."

    Semantic source-side reference (read-only, NOT byte-for-byte ported):
      - acm-plugins/acm-default-plugins/acm-case-file-plugin/src/main/java/
        com/armedia/acm/plugins/casefile/model/CaseFile.java line 141-142:
            @Column(name = "cm_case_status")
            private String status;
        ArkCase's `status` was a free-form String column on the
        `acm_case_file` JPA entity. Any caller could write any string, and
        ArkCase's enumeration of legal values was distributed across
        constants files (CaseFileConstants), the queue handler
        (CaseFileQueueHandler that overrode status to "ACTIVE" pre-save),
        and the state-change service (ChangeCaseFileStateService). The
        ServiceNow target consolidates the enumeration into a Choice list
        in ../choices/sys_choice_case_status.xml and enforces it at the
        platform level via this dictionary entry's choice=3 setting.
      - CaseFile.java line 307-316: @PrePersist hook applied a default of
        "DRAFT" (uppercase) when the status was null/empty. ServiceNow's
        equivalent is the dictionary <default_value>Draft</default_value>
        below. Title Case is intentional per AAP Section 0.1.2.
      - The field name is `status` (lowercase, 6 chars) per AAP Section
        0.5.7 verbatim. This matches conventional ServiceNow Choice-field
        naming across the platform (incident.state, sc_request.state,
        change_request.state - all lowercase).

    Constraints honored (AAP Sections 0.7.1, 0.7.2, 0.7.4):
      - Scope-namespace exclusivity: `<name>` resolves to `x_[scope]_case`
        within the scoped application, and `<sys_scope>` / `<sys_package>`
        bind THIS dictionary record to the same scope by `source` attribute
        lookup. NO global-scope writes - the OOB tables `task`, `incident`,
        `sys_user`, etc. are never modified.
      - Zero hardcoded cross-reference sys_ids: the `<sys_scope>` and
        `<sys_package>` text-node values resolve by scope source name
        (`x_[scope]`), not by literal sys_id. The `<sys_id>`
        text-node value is THIS record's own deterministic primary key
        (MD5 of the canonical field identifier `x_[scope]_case.status`)
        and is NOT a reference to any other record.
      - The literal `[scope]` placeholder is preserved per AAP convention;
        the PDI auto-assigns the actual scope id at App Engine Studio
        creation time.
      - mandatory=true at the dictionary level (AAP Section 0.5.7 verbatim:
        "status | Choice | Draft, Open, In Progress, Pending, Resolved,
        Closed"). Without status the entire state-machine breaks - neither
        per-case-type flow's OnUpdate trigger could match a change in this
        field, the dashboard "Case count by status" donut would have a
        null-status slice, and the "My open cases" report's filter
        (`status NOT IN (Resolved, Closed)`) would return inconsistent
        results. Mandatory enforcement runs at the platform-validation
        level on every insert / update through the standard form, the
        Table API, the scripted REST submission endpoint, and any seed
        scripts.
      - read_only=false: case_manager users and (for some transitions)
        case_agent users edit this field directly to drive transitions.
        ACL-level fine-grained restrictions on WHICH transitions each
        role may perform are enforced by the ACLs in ../acl/ and the
        Flow Designer flows; the dictionary-level read_only flag remains
        false so the field is editable in principle.
      - default_value=Draft (Title Case, NOT "DRAFT", NOT "draft") per
        AAP Section 0.1.2 verbatim. New cases - whether created via the
        internal form, the Table API, the scripted REST submission
        endpoint, or seed scripts - start in Draft status. This default
        is what allows the portal submission endpoint to omit the status
        field from its INSERT payload while still landing the new case
        in Draft as required by AAP Section 0.5.1.
      - audit=true UNIQUELY for this field within this dictionary set.
        Status is the most important field for state-machine forensics:
        every transition through the state graph (Draft -> Open ->
        In Progress -> Pending/Resolved -> Closed) MUST be reconstructable
        after the fact from the sys_audit table for compliance reasons.
        No other field on x_[scope]_case carries audit=true for this POC
        (per AAP Section 0.3.1 minimal-change clause).
      - max_length 40 is sufficient for the longest defined label
        "In Progress" (11 chars) with substantial headroom for future
        statuses - though AAP Section 0.5.7's enumeration is closed-set.
      - choice 3 = "Choice list, no description column" - the standard
        Choice-field configuration when a sibling sys_choice record set
        defines the allowed values.
      - No reference target: this is a String-backed Choice field, not
        a Reference field. All `<reference*>` elements are empty and
        `<table_reference>false</table_reference>`.
      - text_index=false: status is a low-cardinality enumerated Choice
        (six values), so full-text indexing would be wasteful. The
        platform's standard list/report/dashboard surface filters on
        the column directly via GlideRecord addQuery without needing
        a full-text index.
      - No PII: the field stores only categorical lifecycle labels chosen
        from a controlled vocabulary; no real names, email addresses, or
        organizational identifiers are derived from or stored in this
        column.

    Cross-references (AAP Section 0.5.2 dependency ordering):
      - This record MUST load AFTER `../tables/x_[scope]_case.xml`
        (parent table), since `<name>x_[scope]_case</name>` references
        the table by name.
      - This record MUST load BEFORE the consumers that read or write
        the `status` column:
          * ../choices/sys_choice_case_status.xml (the choice values
            Draft, Open, In Progress, Pending, Resolved, Closed -
            which reference this dictionary entry by `name` + `element`
            lookup; the choice ORDER drives dropdown UX with Draft
            first and Closed last)
          * ../flows/general_inquiry_state_machine.xml (OnUpdate trigger
            filtered on status change for type=General Inquiry)
          * ../flows/complaint_state_machine.xml (OnUpdate trigger
            filtered on status change for type=Complaint)
          * ../flows/sub_flows/validate_open_transition.xml (Draft->Open)
          * ../flows/sub_flows/validate_inprogress_transition.xml (Open->In Progress)
          * ../flows/sub_flows/validate_pending_transition.xml (In Progress->Pending)
          * ../flows/sub_flows/validate_resolved_transition.xml (In Progress->Resolved)
          * ../flows/sub_flows/validate_closed_transition.xml (Resolved->Closed)
          * ../business_rules/x_[scope]_block_draft_backtransition.xml (*->Draft prohibited)
          * ../business_rules/x_[scope]_block_terminal_closed.xml (Closed->* prohibited)
          * ../business_rules/x_[scope]_set_closed_date.xml (Resolved->Closed sets closed_date)
          * ../business_rules/x_[scope]_clear_pending_reason_on_inprogress.xml
          * ../script_includes/x_[scope]_CaseTransitionValidator.xml
            (canTransitionToOpen / ToInProgress / ToResolved / ToClosed
            shared static methods)
          * ../portal/rest/sys_ws_definition_x_[scope]_case_status_lookup.xml
            (returns this field as one of the three whitelisted output
            fields per AAP Section 0.7.4: "the lookup page returns ONLY
            status, subject, opened_date")
          * ../portal/rest/sys_ws_definition_x_[scope]_case_submit.xml
            (relies on the default_value=Draft in this entry to land
            new portal-submitted cases in Draft status)
          * ../reports/x_[scope]_my_open_cases.xml (filter:
            `status NOT IN (Resolved, Closed)` AND assigned_agent =
            current user)
          * ../reports/x_[scope]_case_count_by_status.xml (donut grouped
            by this field)
          * ../reports/x_[scope]_all_cases_by_status.xml (bar grouped by
            this field)
          * ../seed-data/cases/x_[scope]_case_demo_*.xml (synthetic demo
            cases that must populate this field with each of the six
            statuses to satisfy AAP Section 0.7.4 minimum-data threshold:
            "every one of the six statuses MUST have at least one demo
            case")
-->
<record_update table="sys_dictionary">
    <sys_dictionary action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE">
